    bibo:volume "4375" ;
    dc:creator "Ramalho, Laís V.; López-Fé, Carlos M.; Rueda, José Luis" ;
    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "Three species of Reteporella (Bryozoa: Cheilostomata) in a diapiric and mud volcano field of the Gulf of Cádiz, with the description of Reteporella victori n. sp" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1158185> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1158185>
    dc:description "FIGURE5. Reteporella victori n. sp. MNCN 25.03/4001.A, general view of the colony fragment; B, general view of a part of the colony showing frontal surface and fenestrulae; C, detail of a branch with fertile and infertile zooids. Note the ong fissure ending in a pseudospiramen; D, close-up of the primary orifice with beaded anter; E, close-up of an oval avicularium with serrated rostrum and small columella on a short cystid; F, triangular avicularium with a trifoliate palate and slightly raised rostrum; G, dorsal side with fenestrulae, sutures and avicularia. Scale bars: A, 4 mm; B, 500 µm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–F, 25 µm, G, 300 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1158185/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

